==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frequency
<hw>Fre"quen*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Frequencies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>frequentia</ets> numerous attendance, multitude: cf. F.
<ets>fr⟦eacute⟧quence</ets>. See <er>Frequent</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The condition of returning frequently; occurrence often repeated;
common occurence; <as>as, the <ex>frequency</ex> of crimes; the
<ex>frequency</ex> of miracles.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The reasons that moved her to remove were, because Rome was a
place of riot and luxury, her soul being almost stifled with, the
<qex>frequencies</qex> of ladies' visits.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A crowd; a throng.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frequent</ent>⟦br⟧
